def restore_square_vertices(x1, y1, x2, y2):
    """
    Description: This function restores the coordinates of the four vertices of a square given x1, y1, x2, y2.
    Input:
    x1 (int): The x-coordinate of the first vertex.
    y1 (int): The y-coordinate of the first vertex.
    x2 (int): The x-coordinate of the second vertex.
    y2 (int): The y-coordinate of the second vertex.
    Output:
    x3 (int): The x-coordinate of the third vertex.
    y3 (int): The y-coordinate of the third vertex.
    x4 (int): The x-coordinate of the fourth vertex.
    y4 (int): The y-coordinate of the fourth vertex.
    """
func_code:
def restore_square_vertices(x1, y1, x2, y2):
    x3 = y3 = x4 = y4 = 0
    if x1 == x2 and y1 == y2:
        return -1, -1, -1, -1

    x3 = x1 + (x2 - x1)
    y3 = y1 + (y2 - y1)
    x4 = x1 - (y2 - y1)
    y4 = y1 + (x2 - x1)
    return x3, y3, x4, y4
